n: Green Hope School Rd Street-Side Trail

d: Green Level Greenway runs from Green Hope School Road and connects up with Brooks Park Greenway to Green Level Church Road.  Along the way it passes nearby to the USA Baseball National Trailing Center and has a spur to the south that leads to Woodlands.
pa: 9008 Green Level Church Road, Cary, NC 27519

d: Swift Creek Greenway goes for a total of 1.2 mi.  One end is along the Kildaire Farm Road Street-Side Trail where there is a pedestrian underpass.  From there the trail passes between Hemlock Bluffs Nature Preserve and Harold D. Ritter Park before coming to Regency Parkway where it connects up with Symphony Lake Greenway across the road.  Parking is available at Ritter Park.

Black Creek Greenway is a 6.5 mi greenway in 3 sections with final pieces in construction which will eventually, along with White Oak Creek Greenway, go all across Cary.  Parking is available at Godbold Park where this 5.5 mi section of greenway passes between the Cary Dog Park and the Sk8-Cary Facility.  Access Northwoods Greenway from here, too.

Black Creek Greenway is a 6.5  mi greenway in 3 sections with final pieces in construction which will eventually, along with White Oak Creek Greenway, go all across Cary.  This location in Bond Park is the hub of the Black Creek/White Oak system where you'll find an interpretive kiosk. Parking is available at the Bond Park Boat House.

Black Creek Greenway is a 6.5  mi greenway in 3 sections with final pieces in construction which will eventually, along with White Oak Creek Greenway, go all across Cary.  Access this 5.5 mi section from this Trailhead Parking Lot.
North Cary Park Greenway begins at the trailhead parking and travels 0.4 mi through the park to connect up with the Black Creek Greenway.

Hinshaw Greenway is a 1.7 mi trail that has Marla Dorrel Park at Thurston Drive at one end and crosses US Hwy 1 on a pedestrian bridge before coming into MacDonald Woods Park and eventually going to Greenwood Circle on the northern end.  It connects to Pirates Cove Greenway via a sidewalk along Glengarry Drive and to Piney Plains Greenway which is a 0.2 spur to Forest Parkway .  Parking is at Marla Dorrel Park or along Seabrook Avenue at MacDonald Woods Park.

White Oak Creek Greenway is a 5.9 mile total greenway which goes from Bond Park to Green Level Church Road in western Cary. Park at Davis Drive Park, cross the road and go north for a short distance along the road to access the trail going west. To go east follow an on-road detour route to pick up the greenway at MacArthur Drive.

White Oak Creek Greenway is a 5.9 mile total greenway which goes from Bond Park to Green Level Church Road in western Cary. This location in Bond Park is the hub of the White Oak/Black Creek Greenway system where you'll find an interpretive kiosk. Parking available at Bond Park Community Center.

Green Hope School Greenway travels for 1.0 mi from Green Hope School Road past Highcroft Elementary School and Sears Farm Park eventually connecting up with the Batchelor Branch Greenway.  Parking is available at Sears Farm Road Park.  The greenway spur traveling west through the park connects up with Highcroft Drive Trail.

Symphony Lake Greenway is a total of 1.8 mi consisting of a loop trail around Symphony Lake, part of which is a 5 sidewalk along Ederlee Drive, crossing a flood plain and ending up on a 10 wide street-side trail along Regency Park Drive ending at Glade Park Road.  Park at the trailhead off of Regency Park Drive near the Koka Booth Amphitheatre.

Louis Stephens Road Trail is a 0.7 mi trail along the edge of the Cary Tennis Park and passing by Green Hope Elementary School and Green Hope School Park where parking is available. There you'll find the 0.4 mile Preston Village Greenway skirting the parks edge.

Annie Jones Greenway is a 1.2 mile total trail that runs from the Cary Parkway up for 0.2 mi where it splits  the east fork going to Gatehouse Drive and the western fork passing through Annie L. Jones Park where parking is available to end at McCloud Court.
Middle Creek Park Greenway is a 0.3 mile greenway within the park which connects up various fields.  It is planned to connect up to the future Camp Branch Greenway system. Parking is available.
pa: 151 Middle Creek Park Avenue, Cary, NC 27539

d: Hinshaw Greenway is a 1.7 mi trail that has Marla Dorrel Park at Thurston Drive at one end and crosses US Hwy 1 on a pedestrian bridge before coming into MacDonald Woods Park and eventually going to Greenwood Circle on the northern end.  It connects to Pirates Cove Greenway via a sidewalk along Glengarry Drive and to Piney Plains Greenway which is a 0.2 spur to Forest Parkway .  Parking is at Marla Dorrel Park or along Seabrook Avenue at MacDonald Woods Park.
Pirates Cove Greenway is 0.7 mi long and goes from Greenwood Circle to Kildonan Place.  It connects to Hinshaw Greenway via a sidewalk along Glengarry Drive.  Park at the end of Greenwood Circle.

This 23 mile rail-trail built on an abandoned railroad corridor stretches from the western edge of Apex passing through Wake, Chatham and Durham Counties on its way to Downtown Durham.  The last unfinished piece, going over Interstate 40 in Durham County is now under construction.  Parking is available at two locations near Cary.
pa: 2584 New Hope Church Road, Cary, NC 27519

d: Mills Park Drive Trail goes for 0.5 mi along the road and spurs off for another 0.3 mi into park facilities at the Mills Park Middle and Elementary Schools.  At the southern end it connects into neighborhoods.  Parking is available in the lot between the softball field and 400 m running track (which is open to the public during non-school hours).

Mills Park Drive Trail goes for 0.5 mi along the road and spurs off for another 0.3 mi into park facilities at the Mills Park Middle and Elementary Schools.  At the southern end it connects into neighborhoods.  Parking is available in the lot between the softball field and 400 m running track (which is open to the public during non-school hours).

Apex Lake Community Greenway  is a 2 mi paved loop trail around the lake which is within Apex Community Park.  It is connected through parking lots on the west side to Laura Duncan Road Street-Side Trail. Parking is available.
Loch Highlands Drive Trail is a 10 wide street-side trail that is 0.9 mi long and goes from Kildaire Farm Road to Penny Road.

Northwoods Greenway goes for 0.8 mi from Chapel Hill Road to Robert V. Godbold Park where it joins up with the Black Creek Greenway.  It passes by the Northwoods Elementary School on one end and at the park ends between the Cary Dog Park and the Sk8-Cary facility. Parking is available at Godbold Park.

Oxxford Hunt Greenway goes for 1.3 mi from along West Chatham Street to meet up with the Black Creek greenway inside Fred G. Bond Park.  It spurs off to the west on the south end of Bond Lake to an unpaved loop trail around the lake that eventually meets back up with the Oxxford Hunt, White Oak Creek and Black Creek greenways. Parking is available at the Bond Park boathouse.
Higgins Greenway is a 0.8 mile trail which starts at SW Maynard Road and ends at Dorothy Park at Union Street.  It also forks off to the west to reach West Chatham Street.
Carramore Avenue Trail is 10 wide street-side trail that goes from Louis Stephens Drive for 0.6 mi before connecting up with the 3.1 mile Davis Drive Trail.
Stone Creek Greenway is a 0.6 mi trail from Carpenter Upchurch Road to Davis Drive.
Kit Creek Greenway goes for 0.4 mi greenway from Morrisville Parkway to April Bloom Lane. Half way is a spur to the east that heads back to Carpenter Elementary.

Green Level Greenway runs for 0.3mi from Green Hope School Road and connects up with Brooks Park Greenway to Green Level Church Road.  Along the way it passes nearby to the USA Baseball National Trailing Center and has a spur to the south that leads to Woodlands Greenway. Plans are for it to head both south and north from Brooks Park. Parking is available at Brooks Park.

Park Village Greenway is a 0.6 mi spur off of the White Oak Creek Greenway between Davis Drive Schools and White Oak Park heading south and is accessible from Park Village Drive. About halfway along it there is another spur to the south called Sherwood Greens Greenway which is 0.3 mi long.
Sherwood Greens Greenway starts at Sherwood Forest Place and travels for 0.3 mi to connect up with Park Village Greenway.
Batchelor Branch Greenway starts at the underpass at NC 55 Highway and travels 0.9 mi to where it meets up with the Green Hope School Greenway.

Green Hope School Greenway travels for 1.0 mi from Green Hope School Road past Highcroft Elementary School and Sears Farm Park eventually connecting up with the Batchelor Branch Greenway. Parking is available at Sears Farm Road Park. The greenway spur traveling west through the park connects up with Highcroft Drive Trail.

Woodlands Greenway is a 1.0 mi trail in two parts that will eventually be connected.  It goes from Mills Road to Ashley Rose Drive and picks up again across the road in the Toscana Subdivision and ends within Thomas Brooks Park where parking is available.

Copperleaf Greenway starts at Green Hope School Road near Copperleaf Place and travels only a short distance before the trail splits. The eastern spur goes to a future 96 acre park and the western spur goes to the American Tobacco Trail. It is a total of 1.1 mi.

Southbridge Greenway runs for 0.6 mi starting at the Morrisville Parkway and traveling to just past Lantern Ridge Road. At that point the greenway is under construction for 0.3 mi to link up to the Cary Park Lake Greenway. It also joins to the 1.0 mi Morrisville Parkway Trail.

Cary Park Lake Greenway is a loop trail that goes for 1.9 mi around the lake. On the south end of the lake the Southbridge Greenway connection is under construction.  On the eastern edge of the lake is an underpass that connects to an existing section of the Green Level Church Road Trail and to the future Mills Park.

Davis Drive Trail is a 10 wide street-side trail that goes for 3.5 miles along the west side of the road.  It connects up to Carramore Avenue Trail, Stone Creek Greenway, and the White Oak Creek Greenway.  It passes by Davis Drive Elementary and Middle Schools and Morrisville Elementary School and connects to the Morrisville Community Park. Find parking at Davis Drive Park.

Indian Creek Greenway is a 1.8 mi greenway that goes from the trailhead park at Morrisville Carpenter Road, where there is parking, to McCrimmon Parkway. Theres a short 0.2 mi spur at Downing Village that will eventually lead to a future 42 acre park at Twin Lakes. This trail is a joint Morrisville/Cary project.

Weston Trail Greenway is a privately built 1.2 mi trail with public access that goes from Norwell Boulevard near North Cary Park to Evans Road at Weston Parkway. Along this trail is a spur that heads north for another 0.4 miles north to Weston Parkway.
Weston Parkway Trail is a 0.8 mi 10 wide street-side trail that spurs off toward the east from Black Creek Greenway, just south of Weston Parkway. It currently terminates at Renaissance Park Place.
Bishops Gate Greenway covers a total of 1.5 miles north and south of Westhigh Street which is a good place to access this neighborhood trail.

Speight Branch Greenway is a 1.3 mi trail that goes from SE Cary Parkway to Walnut Street. On the site of a future 24 acre park a trail/boardwalk loop is now under construction around Macedonia Lake and will connect the trail to the already existing pedestrian tunnel at Tryon Road.
Kildaire Farm Road Trail is a 1.3 mi 10 wide street-side trail giving access along the way to the Hemlock Bluffs Nature Preserve and the Swift Creek Greenway.

Camp Branch Greenway goes for 0.7 mile from TenTen Road to the northern edge of Stanton Place Subdivision which is planned to connect up eventually to Dutchmans Branch Greenway and Oak Grove Elementary and south all the way to Middle Creek School Park.

Dutchmans Branch Greenway is a 0.4 mi trail that goes from Greyhawk Place to the edge of the Greyhawk Subdivision.  It is planned to eventually connect up with Dutchmans Branch Greenway and Oak Grove Elementary.

Churchill Estates Greenway is a 0.8 mi trail that goes along TenTen Road and then through Churchill Estates and is eventually planned to connect up to the future Camp Branch Trail system. It can be accessed from Cambridge Hall Loop.
Westlake Road Trail is a 10 wide street-side trail that winds along for 0.5 mi across the road from Middle Creek High School and the Middle Creek School Park facilities.

Morris Branch Greenway goes for 1.9 mi from New Hope Church Road north around Amberly Lake then east to an existing tunnel under Green Level Church Road where it is planned to cross a future 21 acre park. This greenway is planned to eventually go east all the way to the Historic Carpenter area.

Amberly Lake Greenway is a 0.3 mi trail that connects up around eastern section of Amberly Lake to the Morris Branch Greenway. It goes from Jockey Club Circle up to Yates Store Road.  Future plans are for this greenway to go all the way across the south end of Amberly Lake and connect up there, also, with the Morris Branch Greenway to make a loop.
Nancy Branch Greenway is a 0.8 mi greenway that goes from Summer Harvest Court to Plum Branch Drive divided by a section of the Green Level Church Road Trail at about the middle.

Green Level Church Road Trail is a 10 wide, 1.2 mi long street-side trail that goes along each side of the road with the northern end being at the location of a future 60 acre park.  Plans are for it to eventually connect to the northern end of future Kit Creek Greenway.
